{"name": "wincoll", "metadata": {"name": "wincoll", "version": "0.9", "classifiers": ["Environment :: MacOS X", "Environment :: Win32 (MS Windows)", "Environment :: X11 Applications", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Games/Entertainment :: Puzzle Games"], "home_page": null, "license": "GPL v3 or later", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["importlib_resources", "pygame", "pyscroll", "pytmx", "typing_extensions"], "summary": "Simple rocks-and-diamonds game", "upload_time": 1733786429}, "documentation": ["# WinColl\n\nhttps://github.com/rrthomas/wincoll  \n\nby Reuben Thomas <rrt@sc3d.org>  \n\nWinColl is a simple puzzle game in which you tunnel through caverns\ncollecting diamonds while avoiding being squashed by falling rocks. It is\nbased on [Repton](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Repton_(video_game)) (but\nwithout eggs and monsters).\n\nI originally wrote WinColl for Acorn RISC OS. Original and updated [RISC OS\nversions](<https://github.com/rrthomas/wincoll/RISC OS.md>) are available.\n\n\n## Credits\n\nLevel design and graphics also by Alistair Turnbull, Paul Smith and Jeremy\nDouglas. Paul also designed the title graphic.\n\nThe sounds are from [Freesound](https://freesound.org), lightly adapted:\n\n+ Diamond collection:\n  [Ding.wav by datasoundsample](https://freesound.org/s/638638/) under CC\n  BY 4.0\n+ Rock fall:\n  [WHITE_NOISE-10s.wav by newagesoup](https://freesound.org/s/349315/)\n  under CC 0\n+ Safe unlock:\n  [Old Church Bell (no noise) by igroglaz](https://freesound.org/s/633208/)\n  under CC 0\n+ Death splat:\n  [Splat1.wav by Shakedown_M](https://freesound.org/s/685205/) under CC 0\n\n\n## Installation and use\n\nInstall with `pip`: `pip install wincoll`, then execute the command\n`wincoll`. The game provides instructions on how to play.\n\nYou can edit the levels (the `.tmx` files) with\n[Tiled](https://www.mapeditor.org/).\n\n\n## Copyright and Disclaimer\n\nThe package is distributed under the GNU Public License version 3, or, at\nyour option, any later version. See the file COPYING.\n\nTHIS PROGRAM IS PROVIDED AS IS, WITH NO WARRANTY. USE IS AT THE USER'S RISK.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "wincoll.__main__", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "wincoll.warnings_util", "documentation": ["Warning and error routines.\nCopyright (c) Reuben Thomas 2023.\nReleased under the GPL version 3, or (at your option) any later version."], "functions": [{"name": "wincoll.warnings_util.simple_warning", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "prog", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "...", "xref": null, "params": null}, {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Error messages"]}, {"name": "wincoll.warnings_util.die", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "msg", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "code", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "NoReturn", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.NoReturn", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "wincoll", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python3", "\u00a9 Reuben Thomas <rrt@sc3d.org> 2024", "Released under the GPL version 3, or (at your option) any later version."], "functions": [{"name": "wincoll.die", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "code", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"